WPK Anniversary Observed in Different Countries 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 20 (KCNA) -- Celebration meetings, lectures, round-table talks, book and photo exhibitions and film shows took place in Russia, France, Hungary, Laos, Poland, Uganda, the Czech Republic, Democratic Congo, Brazil and Ecuador from Sept. 26 to Oct. 10 on the occasion of the 60th birth anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 Kriulin, vice-chairman of the Presidium of the "Peace and Today" Committee, at a film show and a book and photo exhibition held in Russia noted that Korea has achieved brilliant successes thanks to the outstanding Songun politics of leader Kim Jong Il who is successfully carrying forward the revolutionary cause of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international secretary of the Central Committee of the Revolutionary Communist League of France said in his speech at a celebration meeting that it is the most prominent exploit in the history of the revolutionary struggle of the working class that Kim Jong Il defeated the extreme offensive of the U.S.-led imperialist allied forces and defended socialism with his Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Juzef Lachut, vice-chairman of the National Executive Committee of the Polish Communist Party, stressed at a meeting that the Korean people are stepping up the building of a great prosperous powerful nation with optimism and confidence in victory of socialism thanks to the unique Songun politics of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seminars on his works "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung" and "The Workers' Party of Korea Organizes and Guides All the Victories of Our People" were held in Guinea, Mexico, Ethiopia and Thailand from Oct. 4 to 8.
 Congratulatory messages to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the meetings held in Hungary, Poland and Guinea.

Solidarity Federation for Part-time Workers Unions Inaugurated in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 20 (KCNA) -- The "National Solidarity Federation of Part-time Workers Unions" was reportedly inaugurated with due ceremony in Seoul on Oct. 16.
 Speakers at the ceremony said that the federation should function as an organization uniting the part-time workers irrespective of region, type of job and form of employment and struggling to ensure the three rights to labor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that as an immediate task they would launch a vigorous campaign for the adoption of a legislation on part-time jobs, united around the organization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The federation released at a press conference a five-point proposal including the total repeal of the "bill on time work" and "law on dispatching workers" and the guarantee of basic rights to labor for the part-timers such as the three rights to labor.

Part-time Workers Demand Legitimate Right in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 20 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions reportedly held a rally to achieve legislation of the right of part-time workers in Seoul on Oct. 16.
 Participating in the rally were more than 8,000 workers under the confederation and representatives of civic and social organizations including the People's Solidarity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Su Ho, chairman of the confederation, and Tan Pyong Ho, national assemblyman from the Democratic Workers' Party, in their speeches called upon all the organizations to unite to win victory, saying that a bill on ensuring the right of part-time workers should be worked out at any cost to settle the issue of part-time jobs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The issue of part-time jobs cannot be settled by checking only, they said, holding that they should achieve the legislation carrying their demands.
 After the rally, the participants marched through streets.

Motive Power for WPK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 20 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of Korea has covered a long path replete with victory and glory, enjoying the absolute trust of the people over the last six decades.
 It is entirely thanks to the ideology and theory on building a revolutionary party expounded by President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il in their famous works.
 Their famous works have been published in "Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works", "Collection of  Kim Il Sung's Works", "Collection of Kim Il Sung's Selected Works", "Collection of Kim Jong Il's Selected Works" and other collections of works. Among them are more than 1,000 works elucidating the revolutionary ideologies and theories on party-building in a scientific way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are encyclopedic works giving perfect answers to all theoretical and practical questions arising in party building and activities in the era of independence on the basis of the great Juche Idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 First of all, they expound the WPK is the Juche-oriented revolutionary Party guided by the immortal Juche Idea. 
 Many works including "Historical Experience of Building the Workers' Party of Korea" and "On the Fundamentals of Revolutionary Party Building" define the character and fighting goal of the Party and the principle and basic direction of its building and activities and give clear-cut answers to the theoretical and practical issues arising in the party building and activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the main ideology running through the works that the monolithic ideological system should be established and a unity and cohesion around leader achieved in the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various works including "On Strengthening the Work of Establishing the Monolithic Ideological System of the Party amongst Cadres and the Work of Revolutionizing Them" and "Let Us Establish Firmer the Monolithic Ideological System in the Whole Party and Society" elucidate the issues relating to the law governing the Party building and activities such as establishing the monolithic ideological system, the basic line of the Party-building, ensuring the unity and cohesion in ideology, will, morality and obligation and the purity of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, many works propound the ideas of enhancing the leading role of the Party as the organizer and guide of all victories, realizing the unique Songun-based revolutionary leadership for the revolutionary Party, building it as a mass and motherly one, correctly solving the issue of succeeding to the revolutionary cause and carrying forward the cause of Party building generation after generation. Typical of them are "The Fundamental Way for Achieving Victory of the Revolution Is to Strengthen the Party and Increase Its Leadership Role", "For Carrying Forward and Accomplishing the Socialist Cause", "The Songun Revolutionary Line Is the Great Revolutionary Line In Our Times and the Ever-victorious Banner of Our Revolution", "Socialism Is a Science" and "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also deal with the Party's policies on opposing invasion and occupation by foreign forces and achieving the unified development of the country and the nation and adhering to the independent line in its foreign policy, defending socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK, Kim Il Sung's Party has won a victory after victory, without any mistake in its lines or fiasco in the implementation of its policies by thoroughly embodying the ideologies and theories on building a revolutionary Party put forward in the works in the party building and activities.

KAPPC on Case of Hyundai Group in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, October 20 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Korea Asia-Pacific Peace Committee Thursday released a statement in connection with the fact that Hyundai Group of south Korea recently divested Kim Yun Gyu, chief director and vice-president of Hyundai Asan who has been a key player in the undertakings for economic cooperation with the north, of all his posts on charge of his alleged "involvement in a scandal," triggering off public furor.
 The statement said the case is a serious matter as it adversely affects not only the relations between Hyundai and the north but overall north-south economic cooperation, adding that yet Hyundai Group side totally dismissed Kim Yun Gyu from his office, inviting strong criticism of the public at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement cited facts to prove that the north takes issue with the case of Hyundai because it sets store by the desire of south Koreans to tour Mt. Kumgang and wishes to remain true to the confidence between the north and Hyundai and the strong sense of obligation towards the predecessors of Hyundai Group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is now no one known to us from Hyundai Group as it has no longer Kim Yun Gyu, who had taken the places of Jong Ju Yong and Jong Mong Hon after their deaths. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hyundai is no longer what used to be as it retains no original appearance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hyundai Group side claims that its removal of Kim from his office was "a measure taken under unavoidable circumstances," but this is nothing but deception and hypocrisy of the coldhearted guys who have gone against the nation's desire and reneged on the bilateral good faith and sense of obligation.
 It is something surprising that the ties of cooperation between the KAPPC and Hyundai based on good faith and sense of obligation have broken up overnight due to a few elements who know nothing about the meaning and peculiarity of the north-south cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now that Hyundai is no longer what used to be and has backpedaled its earlier good faith, there arises doubt as to whether it would function as a counterpart in the cooperation with the north as it did in the past. This, therefore, compels the north to comprehensively examine all undertakings with Hyundai and readjust them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for the issue of tour of Kaesong high on the agenda at the moment, we are not in a position to continue cooperation with Hyundai over this issue and, therefore, compelled to pursue consultation for it with other institutions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "seven-point agreement on cooperation " which the Hyundai side concluded with the KAPPC side in August, 2000 is premised on going through the relevant legal procedures and getting approval by the authorities of both sides and it allows necessary modification, supplementation and re-consultation. 
 As the signatory party is no longer available, there is no reason for us to remain bound to the agreement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This abnormal thing that happened in the relations between the KAPPC and Hyundai is entirely attributable to the Hyundai side's improper behavior.
 Hyundai's unreasonable action seriously marred the significance of the north-south economic cooperation and laid a stumbling block in the way of the cooperation expected to make a fresh leap forward. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hyundai should be held fully responsible for the present situation and all the consequences to be entailed by its ingratitude and indiscreet behavior.
 The GNP should drop its bad habit of viewing others from its own viewpoint. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is still a prospect and a way out for Hyundai. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is our view that if the current situation was created by the higher body of Hyundai against its will, it must feel sorry for it and deeply repent of it.
 If they break with those parasitic high-flyers and take a right path, we will become so generous as to pave a wide avenue for south Koreans' tour of Mt. Kumgang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is our hope that the present higher body of Hyundai will face up to the desire of the nation and the trend of the times and choose a right path.
